 qmail (>= 1.06.3)
Recommends: dsmr-qmail-run (>= 1.0-10),
 vpopmail (>= 5.6.13),
 cron | cron-daemon
Description: system-first recipient routing for hybrid qmail/vpopmail domains
 On a domain that vpopmail owns, qmail-smtpd's chkuser validates every
 recipient against vpopmail only, so mail addressed to a system (shell) user
 is rejected at SMTP time even though qmail-send would deliver it.  This
 package lets one domain serve both shell users and vpopmail virtual users:
 recipients are resolved system-first, then fall through to vpopmail.
 .
 Resolution is dynamic — creating a normal Unix account (home under /home) or
 an ~alias/.qmail-NAME alias is sufficient for that identity to receive mail,
 with no per-user vpopmail alias or qmail assign to provision.  A single
 eligibility predicate is shared by all components so the SMTP-time and
 delivery-time paths cannot disagree.
 .
 The package provides:
   - system-identity, a CLI for the shared eligibility predicate
   - localfirst-rcptcheck, a qmail-smtpd RCPTCHECK validator replacing chkuser
   - localfirst-dispatch, a .qmail-default dispatcher that re-injects system
     recipients and otherwise runs vdelivermail unchanged
 .
 The recipient validator shells out to vpopmail's vrcptcheck for the
 vpopmail-existence check, so it links no vpopmail code and degrades to a pure
 system-identity gate on hosts without vpopmail.  During a vpopmail SQL backend
 outage it defers affected recipients rather than rejecting them.
